{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6ec9-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"862a"},"text":"§ 862a.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Denial of assistance and benefits for certain drug-related convictions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6eca-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"An individual convicted (under Federal or State law) of any offense which is classified as a felony by the law of the jurisdiction involved and which has as an element the possession, use, or distribution of a controlled substance (as defined in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s802/6"},"text":"section 802(6) of this title","children":[],"tail":") shall not be eligible for—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6ecb-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" assistance under any State program funded under part A of title IV of the Social Security Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s601"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 601","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], or"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6ecc-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" benefits under the supplemental nutrition assistance program (as defined in section 3 of the Food and Nutrition Act of 2008 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s2012"},"text":"7 U.S.C. 2012","children":[],"tail":")) or any State program carried out under that Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s2011"},"text":"7 U.S.C. 2011","children":[],"tail":" et seq.]."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6ecd-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Effects on assistance and benefits for others","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6ece-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Program of temporary assistance for needy families","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The amount of assistance otherwise required to be provided under a State program funded under part A of title IV of the Social Security Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s601"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 601","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] to the family members of an individual to whom subsection (a) applies shall be reduced by the amount which would have otherwise been made available to the individual under such part."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6ecf-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Benefits under the Food and Nutrition Act of 2008","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The amount of benefits otherwise required to be provided to a household under the supplemental nutrition assistance program (as defined in section 3 of the Food and Nutrition Act of 2008 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s2012"},"text":"7 U.S.C. 2012","children":[],"tail":")), or any State program carried out under that Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s2011"},"text":"7 U.S.C. 2011","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], shall be determined by considering the individual to whom subsection (a) applies not to be a member of such household, except that the income and resources of the individual shall be considered to be income and resources of the household."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6ed0-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Enforcement","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A State that has not exercised its authority under subsection (d)(1)(A) shall require each individual applying for assistance or benefits referred to in subsection (a), during the application process, to state, in writing, whether the individual, or any member of the household of the individual, has been convicted of a crime described in subsection (a).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6ed1-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Limitations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6ed2-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" State elections","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6ed3-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/d/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Opt out","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A State may, by specific reference in a law enacted after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-08-22"},"text":"August 22, 1996","children":[],"tail":", exempt any or all individuals domiciled in the State from the application of subsection (a)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6ed4-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/d/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Limit period of prohibition","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A State may, by law enacted after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-08-22"},"text":"August 22, 1996","children":[],"tail":", limit the period for which subsection (a) shall apply to any or all individuals domiciled in the State."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6ed5-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Inapplicability to convictions occurring on or before ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-08-22"},"text":"August 22, 1996","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (a) shall not apply to a conviction if the conviction is for conduct occurring on or before ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-08-22"},"text":"August 22, 1996","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6ed6-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" “State” defined","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of this section, the term “State” has the meaning given it—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6ed7-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/e/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in section 419(5) of the Social Security Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s619/5"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 619(5)","children":[],"tail":"], when referring to assistance provided under a State program funded under part A of title IV of the Social Security Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s601"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 601","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6ed8-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/e/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in section 3 of the Food and Nutrition Act of 2008 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s2012"},"text":"7 U.S.C. 2012","children":[],"tail":"), when referring to the supplemental nutrition assistance program (as defined in that section) or any State program carried out under that Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s2011"},"text":"7 U.S.C. 2011","children":[],"tail":" et seq.]."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6ed9-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Rule of interpretation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Nothing in this section shall be construed to deny the following Federal benefits:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6eda-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/f/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Emergency medical services under title XIX of the Social Security Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1396"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 1396","children":[],"tail":" et seq.]."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6edb-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/f/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Short-term, noncash, in-kind emergency disaster relief.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6edc-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/f/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6edd-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/f/3/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Public health assistance for immunizations.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6ede-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/f/3/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Public health assistance for testing and treatment of communicable diseases if the Secretary of Health and Human Services determines that it is necessary to prevent the spread of such disease.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6edf-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/f/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Prenatal care.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6ee0-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/f/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Job training programs.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6ee1-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s862a/f/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Drug treatment programs.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id14ae6ee2-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/193/tI/s115"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–193, title I, § 115","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-08-22"},"text":"Aug. 22, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/2180"},"text":"110 Stat. 2180","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/33/tV/s5516/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–33, title V, § 5516(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-08-05"},"text":"Aug. 5, 1997","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/111/620"},"text":"111 Stat. 620","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/234/tIV/s4115/c/2/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–234, title IV, § 4115(c)(2)(C)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-05-22"},"text":"May 22, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/1109"},"text":"122 Stat. 1109","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/246/s4/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–246, § 4(a)","children":[],"tail":", title IV, § 4115(c)(2)(C), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-06-18"},"text":"June 18, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/1664"},"text":"122 Stat. 1664","children":[],"tail":", 1871; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/79/tIV/s4030/n"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–79, title IV, § 4030(n)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-02-07"},"text":"Feb. 7, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/814"},"text":"128 Stat. 814","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id14ae6ee3-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id14ae6ee4-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id14ae6ee5-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Social Security Act, referred to in subsecs. (a)(1), (b)(1), (e)(1), and (f)(1), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-14/ch531"},"text":"act Aug. 14, 1935, ch. 531","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/620"},"text":"49 Stat. 620","children":[],"tail":". Part A of title IV of the Act is classified generally to part A (§ 601 et seq.) of subchapter IV of chapter 7 of Title 42, The Public Health and Welfare. Title XIX of the Act is classified generally to subchapter XIX (§ 1396 et seq.) of chapter 7 of Title 42. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1305"},"text":"section 1305 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Food and Nutrition Act of 2008, referred to in subsecs. (a)(2), (b)(2), and (e)(2), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/525"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–525","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1964-08-31"},"text":"Aug. 31, 1964","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/78/703"},"text":"78 Stat. 703","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to chapter 51 (§ 2011 et seq.) of Title 7, Agriculture. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s2011"},"text":"section 2011 of Title 7","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id14ae6ee6-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/234"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–234","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/246"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–246","children":[],"tail":" made identical amendments to this section. The amendments by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/234"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–234","children":[],"tail":" were repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/246/s4/a"},"text":"section 4(a) of Pub. L. 110–246","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of the Personal Responsibility and Work Opportunity Reconciliation Act of 1996, and not as part of the Controlled Substances Act which comprises this subchapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id14b0b8d7-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2014—Subsec. (a)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/79/s4030/n/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–79, § 4030(n)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “supplemental nutrition assistance program (as defined in section 3 of the Food and Nutrition Act of 2008 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s2012"},"text":"7 U.S.C. 2012","children":[],"tail":")) or any State program carried out under that Act” for “food stamp program (as defined in section 3("},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":") of the Food Stamp Act of 1977) or any State program carried out under the Food Stamp Act of 1977”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/79/s4030/n/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–79, § 4030(n)(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “supplemental nutrition assistance program (as defined in section 3 of the Food and Nutrition Act of 2008 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s2012"},"text":"7 U.S.C. 2012","children":[],"tail":")), or any State program carried out under that Act” for “food stamp program (as defined in section 3("},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":") of the Food Stamp Act of 1977), or any State program carried out under the Food Stamp Act of 1977”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/79/s4030/n/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–79, § 4030(n)(3)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section 3 of the Food and Nutrition Act of 2008 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s2012"},"text":"7 U.S.C. 2012","children":[],"tail":"), when referring to the supplemental nutrition assistance program (as defined in that section) or any State program carried out under that Act” for “section 3(s) of the Food Stamp Act of 1977, when referring to the food stamp program (as defined in section 3("},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":") of the Food Stamp Act of 1977) or any State program carried out under the Food Stamp Act of 1977”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2008—Subsecs. (a)(2), (b)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/246/s4115/c/2/C/i"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–246, § 4115(c)(2)(C)(i)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section 3("},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":")” for “section 3(h)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/246/s4115/c/2/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–246, § 4115(c)(2)(C)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section 3(s)” for “section 3(m)” and “section 3("},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":")” for “section 3(h)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1997—Subsec. (d)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/33"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–33","children":[],"tail":" substituted “a conviction if the conviction is for conduct” for “convictions”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id14b0b8d8-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"id14b0b8d9-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","at